column2: 2" of rain over last three days.  Southwest wind at 10-15 mph and the temperature is 65-70 degrees.
Cloudy- NW wind at 5-15 mph- and the temperature is 65-70 degrees.
Sunny- SW wind at 5-10 mph- the temperature is in the 70s- and algae bloom starting.
Partly sunny- the temperature is in the 70s- and SE wind at 5-10 mph.
The water color is greenish brown- mostly sunny- 75 degrees- and a light NW wind.
Mostly sunny- upper 70s- and north-northeast wind at 10-15 mph.
Sunny day- boat depth gage 26' from bottom of boat approx. 20" below the surface.
Cloudy-oily looking water- clear bright day- flat surface but still could only get 5' secchi reading.
Algae high made for less reading 5'.  Clear/sunny day- 65 degrees.
Windy- sunny- 60 degrees.  Algae in water.
Air temperature - 65 degrees.  Water temperature + or - 40 degrees- clear water with usual brown color.
Lake and river flowing out is very clear- clearest I've seen it in years.  Can see the bottom from the dock first time.
Water oily- fishing tournament- too many boats out.
Oil from boats- some algae.  Too many boats this month.
Oily water from boats.  Algal bloom.
Full of algae and full of oil from fishing boats over the weekend- overall pretty dirty
Water is extremely clear- 70 degrees- deepest reading- and water temperature is 68 degrees.
Rain on 6/12/98 of 2" and oily water.
Bloom- oily water- and hot at 94 degrees.
Bloom and warm.  End of season.
Shear winds. electricity out for 48 hours.
Lake high. storm damage along shore.
Bloom- muskey fishers- boats on lake
Clear- cool (55 degrees f) - water clear. pollen and caterpillars starting.
Clear- sunny- 70 degrees F. 42 degrees F at night. water contains pollen. loon on lake.
40% clouds- 68 degrees- small waves. Loon at center of lake.
Air 68 degrees F- water surface 66.8 degrees F. rain last 2 days. storm clouds to the ne.
3.5" rain over the weekend. Some clouds- cool - 65 degrees. Water oily looking.
Sunny- air temp 78 degrees F.- sun is hot! water turbid due to boats.
5" rain in dock gauge. 70 degrees- clear- sunny.
Winter is back- 44 degrees last night. clouds- 58 degrees F- water choppy.
Water surface 69.3 degrees.  Air 75 degrees.  Few clouds.  Past several nights 44 to 52 degrees.  No rain.  Too many boats.
Air 80 degrees F- water 71 degrees F- clear. water is like glass- and more water plants as season progresses.
Windy- 30% clouds. air 70 degrees- and Eurasion water milfoil expanding.
Air temp 68 degrees. 80% clouds. strong winds. showers last night.
Water oily- air 68 degrees F.- heavy rain 8/14 - 1"+. water plant parts cut by boats.
Clear- 78 degrees F. air temp-. pollen in water. musky broke the surface. eagle river chain has too many shallow depth 2-3 feet in the river channels. also lake levels too low.
Water temp at 3 feet = 68.9 degrees. Air 80.3 degrees. Light SE wind- chop. Only 1 loon beside me on the lake. Summer is over.
Water surface 66.2 degrees F.- air 63.6 degrees F.  Thin clouds to the west- clear to the east.
Air 73 degrees. water surface 64.4 degrees F. oily cut grass and pollen in the water. boats from musky tournament churned the water. too many boats.
Air 55.3 degrees F.- water surface 57.1 degrees F.- sunny. water riled up- also pollen. 32 degrees F. last 2 nights. water turned over.
Clouds 80%- air 54.5 degrees F.  Surface water 57.2 degrees.  Algae in the water.  One duck- one boat.
Rain all week- the air temperature is 52 degrees- and the water temperature is 38 degrees.
Clouds- the air temperature is 68 degrees- water surface temperature is 61.7 degrees- lake murky due to pollen- and the loon was fishing.
The air temperature is 70 degrees- 0.5" of rain on 6/10- water is clear- few clouds- thunderstorms in area- and water surface temperature is 70 degrees.
The air temperature is 71 degrees- clear- many boats- 6/16 had ground covered with 2" of rain- sun on Wednesday- and DNR should have been spraying.
Hot air at 85-90 degrees- no rain- dry ground- clear water- and heard two loons but none were sighted.
The air temperature is 71.6 degrees- water surface temperature is 72.5 degrees- overcast- the water surface is like glass- and there was rain on 7/15/01.
Southeast breeze- water is oily- several ducks- and sunny with popcorn clouds.
On 7/30 the temperature was 90+ degrees and the dew point was 25- on 7/31 there was 0.75" of rain and the temperature was 80 degrees.  Milfoil cut by boats along shore- something needs to be done.
Great day- the temperature is 90+ degrees- high dew point- the way is should feel in August- and it is overcast.
Milfoil floating in large bundles- the temperature is 70 degrees and it is clear.  What is the DNR doing about the milfoil on the chain
4.5" of rain in the last three days- the air temperature is 56 degrees- the water is cloudy.
The air temperature is 65 degrees and there is pollen in the water.
The air temperature is 62.6 degrees- sunny- green pollen on surface- water temperature same at 18'-30'- three beavers cut shore trees on 9/30- and my lot read 3x.  End of season.
Record cold 5/20 = 21 deg F. Boat in 5/25. Air temp 68.9 deg F. Surface water 55 F. Loon on channel.
Air temp 68 F- surface water 64.4 F-
Air 72 F- surface water 70 F. PMTT - Musky tournament 6/22-23. Milfoil cuttings drifitng downstream. Caterpillars in trees on shoreline.
Air 72 F- Surface 76F. Milfoil cuttings drifting (DNR what are you doing to stop it )
Air temp 64 F- surface water temp 75.8 F. Milfoil starting along shore.
Air temp 62.6 F- Surface water 72.5 F
Water surface 71 F- Air 76 deg F
Surface water 71 F- Air 81 F- At DNR's request no inorganic test for Sept.
Air temp 56.3 F- water 59 F- Rain last 3 days.
Air 49.1 F- Water surface 59 F- The last one for 2002. Have a good winter.
Air 72 F- water surface 70 (ERCLA tests - dissolved O2 saturation 48- biochemical oxygen demand 6 ppm- coliform bacteria yes- pH7- turbidity 40 JTU.
Air 80 F- water surface 74 F.  Milfoil floating down the Chain.
Water surface 73 F- air 82 F- many boats.
Air 80 F- water surface 74 F. 1/2 inch rain 7/10- 11- 2003.
Air 78 F. Water surface 71 F. Nitrate Neg. 4 ppm dissolved oxygen.  46 saturation (poor)- nitrate good- phosphate good.  pH 8.  Turbidity 40 JTU. Good biochemical O2 demand (2ppm).
Air 75 F- water surface 74 F. Many cut weeds- water growth on surface.
Air 78 F- milfoil now in channel off Eagle Lake.  DNR knew of this problem 5 years ago- still no DNR action- why
Air 81.5 F- water surface 78.2 F. Many cut water plants on surface again.
Air 76 F- water surface 77 F. Coliform bact. 20 parts per 100 ml.  Dissolved oxygen 71- nitrate 0- pH 6- turbidity 40 JTU- biochemical oxygen 2 ppm- phosphate 4 ppm.
Air 68 F- water surface 75 F. Coliform bacteria greater than 20 coliform colores/100 ml in Eagle- Duck- Cranberry Lakes.
Air 68 F- water surface 70 F. Pollen on water.
Air 69 F- water surface 69 F. Dissolved oxygen 45- nitriate 0- pH 7- Biochemical O2 BOD - 2ppm- phosphate 1 ppm- turbidity 40.
Cold- 38 F- water surface 50 F.  Dissolved Oxygen 73 ppm- phosphate 2 ppm- pH 7- nitrate 0. Turbidity 40 JTU- biochemical oxygen demand 2 ppm - good- 20 F last night. Boats out.
Air 70.2 F- water surface 66 F.  Since last reading- cold - rain windy.  Strong wind today.  pH 7- nitrate 0.  Biochemical O2 demand 1 ppm- phosphate 1 ppm.  Dissolved O2 68%.
Air 69 F- water surface 64 F- windy- cold with rain past week.  40 F night - 60s days.
Water surface 66 F- air 70 F.  First nice boating day in a month.  Rain gauge .75".  Rain/cold so far in July.
Air 68 F- water surface 69 F.  pH 8- phosphate 1 ppm- nitrate 0- dissolved oxygen 6.9 ppm.
Water surface 70 F- air 72 F- 1 1/4 " rain 8/8/04.  More milfoil.
Water surface 68 F- Air 70 F.  Frost 8/12.  Milfoil - no DNR help- why
Air 61.7 F- water surface 65.8 F.  Took temp. reading twice - put in new batter - same results.  Coliform bacteria - negative- pH 6- dissolved oxygen 21 PPM.
Water surface 68 F- Pollen- green.  Air 70 F.
Air 72 F- pollen on water surface.  68 F.  Milfoil (cut) on water surface.
Air 69 F- water surface 67 F.  After Labor Day weekend- I've filled bags with cut milfoil around my dock.
Air 53.6- water surface 52.5 F.  Cold.  Pollen on water surface.  End of summer of 2004.
Water surface 67 F- air 72 F- clear- sunny.
Air 78 F- water surface 75 F.  Fishing tournament. More cut milfoil on surface.
Air 72 F.  Water surface 70 F.  Boat broken - milfoil plugged the water intake on motor - overheated.  Paddled back to dock.
Air 60 F.  Water surface 72 F.  New training manual for lake monitoring excellent - better than the old one - Thanks.
Air 70 F.  Water surface 79 F.  Motor outboard repaired so I can start taking readings again.
Air 78 F.  Water surface 79 F.  More milfoil in area.
Water surface 74 F- air 70 F.  Cut weeds on surface - milfoil.
Air 70 F- water surface 74 F- new spot of milfoil in channel - DNR
This ends the 10th year we have taken readings.  Reported milfoil each year - no DNR response.  We quit in protest!
hot sunny day- about 88 for temp
calm winds with temp about 65. A day after some high winds all day.  Ice-out in 2007 was Apr. 19th.

Checked some of the milfoil weed beds around the lake. EMW are mostly about 4 to 6 inches under water- with a few on top. Getting dark brown and algae on leaflets. Sunny- but hazy day- with about 10mph winds.
Shoreline a little green. A lot of geese flying south today.  temp 74 with light wind.
What a nice day- calm warm winds- with a demp of 86.
almost 2 weeks of rain every day. today sunny- 48. water alittle green with a lot of small 5 inch chunks of alge flooting on top of water.
First day we had with light winds- after ice out which was on Apr. 30th on Eagle Lake.
Algea just starting on top of water. Bright and calm sunny day. about 82
Very few cut-up weeds on top of water for this time of year. Partly sunny day- about 83. Seen 4 eagles and 3 loons.
Lt. wind- cloudy and temp about 80
Lt. wind- sunny and temp about 86.
